{[%evp 0,33,30,35,28,-16,20,10,-14,-14,2,-67,10,-7,-6,-42,-36,-30,35,35,34,25,25,25,46,46,46,44,52,33,35,35,72,-12,24,23] [#]} {[%tqu "En","Dreev-Christensen, 2003. White to move.","","","g4h3","The only interesting move—I found it back in 2003! We stop Black from castling long.",10,"g4g7","Very risky.",0]} 16. Qh3 $1 {The only interesting move—I found it back in 2003! We stop Black from castling long.} (16. Qxg7 $6 {Very risky.} O-O-O $1 $36 {Black has full compensation and maybe some initiative.}) 16... a5 $1 $146 {Engine idea.} (16... Bxb3 $2 {was my opponent's reply.} 17. Nxb3 $16 {[%csl Re8,Rh5] White is better just because Black's pawn on h5 is misplaced, and Black needs to spend time to castle.}) 17. Rac1 a4 18. Nf5 Qg5 19. Nbd4 {Black must find the only move, otherwise much worse.} O-O-O $3 $13 {I don't believe that it is an easy move to play.} *

